Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[Eyecatch]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.02,0:00:05.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Dragged along by Ran, Sonoko, and \NSera so they could buy new swimsuits
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.80,0:00:10.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,to go to the pool, I arrived \Nat the department store.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.68,0:00:13.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But once there...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.92,0:00:29.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The victim was cosmetics company \Npresident Sashihara Ritsuko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.30,0:00:29.80,Ritsuko,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Sashihara Ritsuko (41) \NCustomer
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.82,0:00:34.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The index finger and thumb on the \Nbody's left hand were extended,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.86,0:00:39.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and her own red lipstick \Nwas on her right thumbnail.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.47,0:00:43.31,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.06,0:00:45.60,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,For what purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.89,0:00:51.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Curtains rise as the headliner appears!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.92,0:00:54.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He beautifully dances his \Nmystery-solving steps!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.36,0:00:56.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The shape of her fingers and red lipstick.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.31,0:00:58.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sera's secret is hidden \Nwithin the mysterious case.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.70,0:01:00.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.20,0:01:02.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.11,0:01:04.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.01,0:02:51.02,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(405,1)}The Blind Spot in the Changing Room \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.71,0:02:48.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Blind Spot in the \NChanging Room, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.01,0:02:54.02,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.23,0:02:57.00,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The order in which \NSashihara-sama, Yamaki-sama,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.27,0:02:59.40,Reia,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Nanbu Reia (24) \NEmployee
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.00,0:02:59.40,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}and Nitsuka-sama entered the changing rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.58,0:03:00.58,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.58,0:03:05.91,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,I think Yamaki-sama was first.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.38,0:03:09.92,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,She said she'd forgotten where \Nthe changing rooms were,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.32,0:03:12.92,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,so I showed her the way \Nto the front of the rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.10,0:03:15.96,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see the white sandals then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.96,0:03:19.52,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,I believe they were already in \Nfront of the room on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.95,0:03:24.38,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,Sashihara-sama was next.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.38,0:03:27.43,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,She entered the empty room in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.67,0:03:29.15,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.15,0:03:31.80,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So Nitsuka-san was last?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.80,0:03:32.69,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.05,0:03:37.72,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,She entered quite a while \Nafter Sashihara-sama,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.72,0:03:40.44,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,and was irritated that none \Nof the rooms were freeing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.66,0:03:46.12,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,According to Conan-kun, Sashihara-san \Nsaid something rather harsh to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.12,0:03:47.20,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.68,0:03:50.66,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,But a senior employee told me
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.66,0:03:55.07,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,she'd been told the same thing \Nbefore and not to worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.45,0:03:59.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The dead woman said something
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.55,0:04:03.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,that made it sound like you \Nmet for the first time today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.06,0:04:06.51,DCItalic,SASHIHARA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't recognize you. Are you new?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.30,0:04:10.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But you actually met a week ago, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.36,0:04:11.56,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.56,0:04:16.52,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,She was here with Yamaki-sama when \NNitsuka-sama collapsed in the changing room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.08,0:04:21.19,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Are the black pumps you're \Nwearing and those white sneakers
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.19,0:04:23.20,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,the only shoes you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.20,0:04:24.40,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.40,0:04:26.91,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,I keep the pumps in my locker,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.10,0:04:29.91,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,and usually wear these sneakers to commute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.12,0:04:32.75,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Those are really all you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.75,0:04:37.29,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,If you think I'm lying, \Nyou can search the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.57,0:04:43.36,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Nanbu-san, could you draw \Nthe white sandals you saw?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.36,0:04:46.01,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't need to be detailed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.01,0:04:47.85,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.06,0:04:49.15,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.10,0:04:53.35,Ayami,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Yamaki Ayami (35) \NCustomer
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.15,0:04:53.35,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Like the employee said, the white sandals
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.49,0:04:56.01,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,were already there when I \Nentered the changing room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.20,0:05:01.86,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,President Sashihara entered the \Nchanging room next to yours later.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.10,0:05:05.06,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear any strange noises?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.06,0:05:06.61,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,No, not in particular.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.86,0:05:10.54,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure you didn't offer to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.54,0:05:12.74,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,help her undress and enter her room?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.74,0:05:14.89,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I do that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.89,0:05:16.62,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not her servant!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.82,0:05:19.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But the president said
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.90,0:05:23.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,she took on your debt and hired you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.94,0:05:28.51,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's true that I wasn't her equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.87,0:05:31.07,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,But you saw her clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.07,0:05:34.77,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't need help to remove them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.96,0:05:36.34,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.34,0:05:37.61,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,By the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.61,0:05:41.98,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,are those boxes you had inside \Nyour bag a gift for someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.98,0:05:44.92,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, for the president \Nof the department store.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.92,0:05:47.74,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's one of our new products.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.74,0:05:52.53,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,President Sashihara told me to have \None of the employees give it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.78,0:05:55.34,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to check the contents?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.34,0:05:57.72,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's just perfume.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.72,0:06:00.55,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.55,0:06:04.70,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Also, could you draw us a \Npicture of the white sandals?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.70,0:06:07.21,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't have to be precise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.21,0:06:09.05,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.25,0:06:10.55,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.30,0:06:13.68,Tomoya,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Nitsuka Tomoyo (43) \NCustomer
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.55,0:06:13.68,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I collapsed in the changing \Nroom here last week
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.07,0:06:18.50,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,because of the dog hair that \NSashihara woman left everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.50,0:06:21.69,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You're allergic to dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.89,0:06:23.79,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,According to forensics,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.79,0:06:28.20,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,they found substantial quantities \Nof dog hair in the changing room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.20,0:06:29.11,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.33,0:06:30.27,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.27,0:06:33.35,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know when the owner \Nof the white sandals
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.35,0:06:35.66,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,left the changing room?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.02,0:06:39.73,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Between 2:43 PM and 2:44 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.73,0:06:41.79,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,I was checking every minute
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.17,0:06:45.26,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,to see if the room on the right was open.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.48,0:06:48.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Why the room on the right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.69,0:06:52.14,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,That dog-hair-covered \Nwoman was in the middle,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.14,0:06:53.94,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,and her employee was in the left room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.94,0:06:56.81,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Her employee could have dog hair on her, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.01,0:07:01.44,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So you knew the victim \Nentered the middle room?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.44,0:07:03.56,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.74,0:07:08.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's that light brown case thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.29,0:07:09.49,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.91,0:07:12.88,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,They're folding slippers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.88,0:07:16.24,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm taking a flight to China after this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.51,0:07:22.45,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you made those slippers \Nlook like white sandals...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.45,0:07:23.42,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.61,0:07:26.23,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Look at them! They're beige!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.23,0:07:29.51,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,What we saw were white sandals \Nshaped totally differently!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.51,0:07:30.62,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.62,0:07:32.15,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Give me that paper and pen!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.15,0:07:34.39,DCMain,NITSUKA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll draw what they looked like!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.81,0:07:40.35,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,All three of them are \Nalmost exactly the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.58,0:07:44.78,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It seems there really was a \Ncustomer wearing white sandals.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.78,0:07:45.96,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.54,0:07:50.35,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Forensics found scissors, bits of tape,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.35,0:07:52.69,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,and pieces of a straw in a garbage can
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.69,0:07:56.01,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,near the changing rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.01,0:07:58.53,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think they're connected to the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.81,0:08:03.70,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,They still don't know who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.70,0:08:04.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.51,0:08:05.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The killer is probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.62,0:08:08.34,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,That woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.49,0:08:10.96,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,No way. You already figured it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.17,0:08:12.07,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.07,0:08:16.86,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,But I still don't know how they \Nentered the victim's changing room
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.86,0:08:18.40,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,without her causing a commotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.40,0:08:22.28,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The victim was probably wearing a face cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.28,0:08:23.08,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.08,0:08:27.36,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,those disposable ones so your makeup \Ndoesn't get on the merchandise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.67,0:08:30.91,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You can't see very well \Nwhen you're wearing one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.91,0:08:33.12,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But they don't make you blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.12,0:08:35.36,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You'd be able to tell if someone entered.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.55,0:08:39.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do they have those in the changing rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.25,0:08:44.39,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Some stores hand them out before you enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.88,0:08:48.40,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,A lot of stores keep them \Nin the rooms themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.40,0:08:50.50,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like a big tissue box.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.94,0:08:53.30,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.76,0:08:55.34,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.19,0:09:00.10,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,This wasn't the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.48,0:09:03.57,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was the second murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.66,0:09:10.82,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.10,0:09:14.68,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We checked the store's security cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.68,0:09:17.14,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Many of the customers' feet weren't visible,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.14,0:09:18.93,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,and we weren't able to find anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.93,0:09:22.26,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,wearing the white sandals \Nthe three women saw
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.26,0:09:25.58,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,in front of the right changing \Nroom at the time of the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.70,0:09:30.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the customer wearing the sandals
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.04,0:09:32.13,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,was the killer and has already left.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.13,0:09:35.70,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Or the store employee, Nanbu Reia-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.70,0:09:37.51,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,who discovered the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.99,0:09:42.82,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Or the victim's employee, Yamaki Ayami-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.82,0:09:47.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,who was using the left \Nroom before the victim
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.16,0:09:49.02,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,entered the middle room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.37,0:09:53.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Or the woman allergic to \Ndogs, Nitsuka Tomoyo-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.55,0:09:57.10,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,who entered the room on the right after
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.10,0:09:59.78,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,the customer wearing white sandals left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.21,0:10:05.70,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The question is how did the killer \Nget inside the changing room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.70,0:10:06.54,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.72,0:10:10.76,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The victim would've said something if \Nsomeone entered while she was changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.76,0:10:14.05,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,And even if they snuck in...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.40,0:10:18.22,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The killer's reflection should've \Nappeared in this mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.22,0:10:19.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.48,0:10:22.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If the victim was already unconscious
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.74,0:10:26.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,when the killer entered the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.61,0:10:28.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,she wouldn't have been able to say anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.20,0:10:30.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and it would've been easy to strangle her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.12,0:10:32.62,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The victim was unconscious?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.62,0:10:33.94,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.26,0:10:38.29,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Using one of the face covers on the \Nright side of the changing room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.89,0:10:41.30,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Men probably don't recognize them,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.30,0:10:46.10,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,but female customers wear them when trying \Non clothes so their makeup doesn't get on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.10,0:10:47.33,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.57,0:10:51.54,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,By soaking the face covers in chloroform,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.54,0:10:56.34,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,the victim knocked herself out \Nfor the killer by putting on one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.34,0:10:58.28,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.20,0:11:02.39,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I didn't know \Nabout face covers either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.39,0:11:05.72,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was a giant tissue box.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.35,0:11:10.51,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So the killer had a bottle of chloroform.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.51,0:11:12.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't have to be a bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.06,0:11:13.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A straw's more than enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.95,0:11:15.11,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,A straw?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.29,0:11:20.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You melt one end of a \Nstraw using a hair iron,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.48,0:11:23.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,pour the chloroform into the open end,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.64,0:11:27.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and melt the open end.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.32,0:11:32.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,To use it, you just have to cut \None end open with scissors.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.34,0:11:34.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I read online that it's a convenient way
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.47,0:11:37.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,to store cosmetics to reduce \Nyour luggage while traveling.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.50,0:11:42.55,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what the straw and scissors \Nwe found near the crime scene were for.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.82,0:11:44.90,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go check with forensics.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.22,0:11:51.40,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But even if the face covers \Nwere soaked in chloroform,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.40,0:11:56.06,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,the killer had to know which changing \Nroom the victim would enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.42,0:12:00.02,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,She'd enter the middle room \Nif it were the only one free.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.02,0:12:03.07,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But another customer could enter the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.40,0:12:08.28,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. The killer made her \Nfirst attempt last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.76,0:12:11.00,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,And like you said,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.00,0:12:15.33,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Nitsuka-san entered the \Nroom before the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.70,0:12:18.87,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, this was her \Nsecond attempt at murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.87,0:12:23.08,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So Nitsuka-san collapsed a week ago
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.08,0:12:24.74,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,not because of her dog allergy,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.74,0:12:27.10,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,but because she smelled the chloroform.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.44,0:12:31.14,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But how did she leave the middle room open?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.14,0:12:32.85,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The killer could enter one room,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.85,0:12:37.11,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,but how did she block the other?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.32,0:12:41.70,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,By putting the white sandals \Nin front of the other room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.43,0:12:47.12,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,This could only have been \Ndone by the woman
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.39,0:12:49.87,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,who entered the left room before \Nthe victim entered the middle room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.54,0:12:53.12,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Yamaki Ayami-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.12,0:12:54.62,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.40,0:13:00.35,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.35,0:13:03.26,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any white sandals!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.64,0:13:08.11,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, the sandals were there \Nbefore I entered the changing room!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.11,0:13:09.65,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Right, miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.65,0:13:11.36,DCMain,NANBU,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.36,0:13:12.69,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.58,0:13:18.10,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,We bought insoles, tape, and a white ribbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.10,0:13:19.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.43,0:13:22.48,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What's this stuff for?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.68,0:13:26.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to make another customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.04,0:13:28.76,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Another...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.76,0:13:29.99,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Customer?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.11,0:13:38.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,First place the white ribbon against
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.32,0:13:40.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the heel of the insole.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.53,0:13:45.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Cross the ribbon on the underside \Nof the insole and tape it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.67,0:13:49.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then cross the ribbons over the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.09,0:13:53.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Tape the ends to the \Nunderside again and there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.90,0:13:57.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You have some white sandals.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.32,0:13:58.32,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.32,0:14:00.24,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Not bad, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.77,0:14:03.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm good at arts and crafts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.15,0:14:06.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Make a second one, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.17,0:14:09.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Put them in front of the changing room,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.18,0:14:12.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and it looks like someone's inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.18,0:14:17.25,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't it be obvious since \Nthey're so flat and heel-less?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.44,0:14:22.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But if you raise the heel by \Nplacing a cell phone under them...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.56,0:14:26.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,See? They look like sandals from above.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.50,0:14:27.88,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.19,0:14:29.90,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You had one, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.52,0:14:33.51,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,A present wrapped in white ribbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.44,0:14:39.42,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,If you made the sandals beforehand \Nand kept them in your bag,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.42,0:14:45.02,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,all that would be left after the murder \Nwould be the tape you used to make the sandals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.28,0:14:47.67,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You could tie the ribbon around the present,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.67,0:14:51.41,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,and you could hide the insoles \Ninside your own shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.64,0:14:53.03,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.03,0:14:56.89,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The bits of tape we found \Nwith the straw and scissors
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.89,0:15:00.58,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,were from when she removed \Nthe ribbon from the insoles.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.58,0:15:05.25,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Her fingerprints may be on the tape since \Nit's difficult to remove without bare hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.52,0:15:08.76,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Here's what you did:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.26,0:15:13.27,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,After making sure the three \Nchanging rooms were empty,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.27,0:15:17.26,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,you placed the white sandals in \Nfront of the room on the right,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.26,0:15:22.02,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,told an employee you forgot \Nwhere the changing rooms were,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.02,0:15:26.11,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,had her show you, and made sure she saw \Nthe white sandals in front of the right room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.68,0:15:29.03,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,When the employee returned to the store,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.03,0:15:31.03,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,you entered the middle room,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.64,0:15:36.37,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,soaked a face cover in the \Nchloroform you had in the straw,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.90,0:15:40.87,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,put it back in the box, \Nand entered the left room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.08,0:15:45.13,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You watched through the curtain \Nfor the victim to enter
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.39,0:15:48.38,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,and listened for the victim \Nto inhale the chloroform
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.38,0:15:50.54,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,in the face cover and collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.04,0:15:55.04,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,After making sure no one was around,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.04,0:15:58.26,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,you entered the middle room,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.65,0:16:01.64,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,wrapped the rope you brought \Naround the victim's neck,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.38,0:16:04.40,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,and strangled her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.73,0:16:08.96,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Then you waited for Nitsuka-san, who was \Nfrequently checking the changing rooms,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.96,0:16:11.77,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,to return to the store,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.77,0:16:14.41,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,reached through the curtain to collect
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.41,0:16:17.41,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,the white sandals and cell phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.97,0:16:21.92,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,listened for Nitsuka-san \Nto enter the right room,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.92,0:16:24.92,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,returned to the left room,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.92,0:16:29.26,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,removed the ribbon from the white \Nsandals, tied it around the present,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.26,0:16:32.67,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,and put the insoles inside your own shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.10,0:16:37.38,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You intended to leave the \Nchanging room immediately,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.38,0:16:42.10,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,but an employee found the \Nvictim's body first, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.60,0:16:47.90,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Then what were those shapes the \Nvictim made with her hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.14,0:16:53.09,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,The right hand grasping her \Nthumb with lipstick on it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.09,0:16:54.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The national flag.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.37,0:16:55.32,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The national flag?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.49,0:16:58.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, the flag of China.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.26,0:17:03.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The victim was wearing nails \Nwith five stars on them,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.36,0:17:06.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so by making the area around the stars red,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.04,0:17:09.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,she was trying to make it \Nlook like the Chinese flag.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.29,0:17:12.34,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,B-But why China?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.53,0:17:16.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Chinese people count on their \Nfingers in an unusual way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.89,0:17:19.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They count from one to ten on a single hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.47,0:17:21.19,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,One hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.19,0:17:24.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,One through five are the same as Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.58,0:17:27.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but this is six, and this is seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.60,0:17:30.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And this is eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.40,0:17:33.03,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait. Isn't that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.66,0:17:36.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.40,0:17:39.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Eight, for the "Ya" in Yamaki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.63,0:17:43.52,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.52,0:17:46.63,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Since the victim was well-traveled,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.63,0:17:50.33,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,she knew how they count in China.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.33,0:17:54.92,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Since the changing room floor \Nis covered in dog hair,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.48,0:17:57.81,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,you'll probably find a couple strands
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.81,0:18:02.68,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,on the bottoms of Yamaki-san's feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.78,0:18:10.56,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to look for dog hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.76,0:18:15.82,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I was the president's pet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.09,0:18:17.54,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Her pet?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.54,0:18:22.08,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I came here to buy clothes a few \Nmonths ago with the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.42,0:18:26.00,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,We happened to try on the same clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.00,0:18:27.08,DCItalic,SASHIHARA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.38,0:18:30.83,DCItalic,SASHIHARA,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to wear that \Nto the upcoming party?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.02,0:18:32.31,DCItalic,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.31,0:18:36.51,DCItalic,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,But if you planned to wear it, \NI'll choose something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.51,0:18:38.77,DCItalic,SASHIHARA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.77,0:18:40.56,DCItalic,SASHIHARA,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be wearing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.56,0:18:42.46,DCItalic,SASHIHARA,0000,0000,0000,,You wear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.46,0:18:44.01,DCItalic,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.41,0:18:46.74,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like a nice president.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.74,0:18:48.26,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.26,0:18:51.15,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,The president didn't wear \Nthose clothes herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.07,0:18:57.40,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,She had them remade as dog clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.29,0:18:59.90,DCItalic,SASHIHARA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my, Yamaki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.24,0:19:02.84,DCItalic,SASHIHARA,0000,0000,0000,,You and my dog are matching.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.84,0:19:05.56,DCItalic,SASHIHARA,0000,0000,0000,,That choker looks like a collar, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.56,0:19:08.35,DCItalic,SASHIHARA,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I attach a lead to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.59,0:19:16.55,DCItalic,SASHIHARA,0000,0000,0000,,You're my pet for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.66,0:19:24.45,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't get a new job
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.45,0:19:27.37,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,because of the debt I owed the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.86,0:19:31.31,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,So I killed her before she could kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.54,0:19:35.06,DCMain,YAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,So I wouldn't be hers forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.48,0:21:05.78,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Case closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.04,0:21:09.95,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,With me and Conan-kun on the case, \Na case like that is a cinch.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.18,0:21:11.46,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.46,0:21:15.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A-All I did was make sandals using a ribbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.60,0:21:18.12,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Impressive as always, high school detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.12,0:21:20.48,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko, you're a high school detective, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.48,0:21:22.63,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You called yourself the Mystery Queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.87,0:21:26.88,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't had any epiphanies lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.27,0:21:31.27,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I used to feel them right \Naround the back of my neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.27,0:21:34.89,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I haven't tranquilized \NSonoko in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.18,0:21:36.91,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I had no idea
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.91,0:21:40.60,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,they count like this in Germany and France.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.60,0:21:43.65,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi used to do that all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.24,0:21:47.07,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,He said he got it from his mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.37,0:21:52.17,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Mom tried to act cool \Nby mimicking French people.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.17,0:21:53.96,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.56,0:21:57.00,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Is this how they count to three in Europe?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.00,0:22:01.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No. I saw on TV that even in \NEurope, there are exceptions.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.96,0:22:04.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,England is the same as Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.19,0:22:08.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They count to three using \Ntheir pointer finger,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.17,0:22:11.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,middle finger, and ring finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.07,0:22:13.75,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.75,0:22:16.35,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it. Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.21,0:22:23.06,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,During the Red Woman case, Sera...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.62,0:22:26.46,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,That's a pretty thin bat, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.46,0:22:28.61,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Can you hit a ball with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.82,0:22:30.69,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Said something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.69,0:22:35.51,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she was thinking of cricket \Nsince that's popular in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.02,0:22:39.62,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Cricket bats are flatter and \Nthicker than baseball bats.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.14,0:22:45.12,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And according to American manners, \Nafter cutting your food with a knife,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.12,0:22:46.78,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,you switch your fork to your right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.18,0:22:51.14,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You eat with your fork in your \Nleft hand in Japan and England.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.08,0:22:53.60,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.60,0:22:55.89,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't Sera say this, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.48,0:23:01.52,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,That's how I know Conan-kun's \Npretty good at football.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.16,0:23:06.03,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Americans don't call soccer "football."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.43,0:23:10.91,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Which means Sera studied in England,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.91,0:23:12.78,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,not America.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.42,0:23:16.96,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But why is she lying about going to England?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.56,0:23:20.79,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.84,0:23:22.86,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,England...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.93,0:23:28.17,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,England...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.80,0:23:33.05,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,England...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.26,0:23:37.35,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.29,0:23:41.82,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I remember now!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:24:09.05,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.15,0:23:51.32,DCMain,OTAGURO,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, you came. I've been waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.51,0:23:55.32,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, did you guys just see something yellow?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.55,0:23:58.33,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I did. It disappeared immediately, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.66,0:24:02.21,DCMain,SABURO,0000,0000,0000,,The master says there are ghosts.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.08,0:24:06.07,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.05,0:24:15.05,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Detective Boys and the Haunted House
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.69,0:24:13.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "The \NDetective Boys and the Haunted House!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.07,0:24:35.07,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Greenhouse
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.50,0:24:32.66,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.06,0:24:34.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A greenhouse!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.07,0:24:36.04,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Remember anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.07,0:24:40.08,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.04,0:24:37.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yeah, a beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.17,0:24:38.33,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}When and where?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.33,0:24:39.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It's a secret.
